research_municipality_step.notes: Fate, TX operates under a Council-Manager form of government. The City Council consists of a Mayor and six Council members, all elected by the entire city. After elections, Council members select the Mayor Pro Tem and Deputy Mayor Pro Tem from among themselves. The provided information reflects the current elected officials as of January 2026, based on the latest available data from the city's official website and the TML City Officials Directory. There are mentions of upcoming elections in May 2025 and a recall effort for Councilwoman Codi Chinn, but the current officials are listed above.
